+# Independent design — <cycle-id>
+
+date: <YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ>
+generated_by: Codex Pass A (blind, no Claude plan in context)
+codex_session: <session-id>
+codex_model: <model name>
+
+<This file is generated by /second-opinion's Pass A step for Tier 1
+cycles. It is Codex's OWN independent design for the problem, written
+BEFORE Codex sees Claude's plan. It serves as the reviewer's reference
+during Pass B (the comparison review).
+
+DO NOT EDIT this file by hand. It is regenerated each Tier 1 cycle.
+
+The point of this artifact: anchoring-resistance. When Codex reviews
+Claude's plan in Pass B, it has its own design in context as the
+reference, so its critique is anchored against its own thinking, not
+against Claude's framing.>
+
+## Goals
+
+<Codex's statement of what the change should achieve. 3 sentences.>
+
+## Approach
+
+<Codex's high-level approach. 3-5 sentences.>
+
+## Key decisions
+
+<Codex's decisions on the major design choices. Each with reasoning.
+
+Examples:
+- Use ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE rather than MERGE because of concurrency.
+- Add idempotency_key column to handle retries.
+- Single transaction for the schema migration; rollback if any step fails.
+>
+
+## Trade-offs
+
+<What Codex would accept and what it would reject. This is the
+reviewer's stance on the cost/benefit of the design.>
+
+### Accepted
+- <trade-off 1>
+
+### Rejected
+- <trade-off 2>
+
+## Test strategy
+
+<Codex's view on what tests should exist. Aligned with the project's
+testing conventions in CLAUDE.md and the project's Tier 1 discipline.>
